reviewText: very good collection
I'm buying all the volumes so that I can have them for my collection. I loved this show and I will always watch them.
Super fun and clean humor.  Again, nostalgia for our earlier years. Clever way they slip in advertisements at beginning and end of show.

This was an OK collection because it was mixed with the boys old and young...meaning it was not in sequence. I didn't think it was put together well enough where I'd buy any more. I bought a few all at once thinking they were arranged by season, and was disappointed that they were not. I was not familiar with this series as a child, and looked forward to watching the first episode through the last....sorry to say, I am not sure that I even saw the first episode! Also there was too much of the older boy (David?) and his married life to his wife - forgot her name - and found it rather hum-drum. I was more interested in the first seasons, simply because I wanted to see why it had become popular to begin with....I never figured out why.
They don't make them like this any more and never will.  We have all three sets and love them all.

i watched this tv show during the 50's and 60's. i grew up with ricky nelson. i loved to listen to his records. since i have amazon prime i got free shipping on this product. watching this tv show will transport you back to a time when things were simpler. amazon has lots of vintage tv shows. check them out. happy shopping. aloha haleiwa jon

These episodes of the Adventures of Ozzie and Harriet are as much fun and as timely now as they were in the 1950s when I was a child. Human nature doesn't change and the humor that accompanies family situations is funny from generation to generation. Clever dialogue, humor, and good clean fun for the whole family.

If I were you, I'd wait because a much better collection is on its way (roughly Dec. 2014).
Sam Nelson (Ricky Nelson's son) is actually raising money to restore the entire 435-episode series of "The Adventures of Ozzie and Harriet" and include the original commercials too!  He hopes to have the entire series restored by the time "The Adventures of Ozzie and Harriet" is inducted into the Smithsonian.
Loved
Great stories! Some are repetitive, but enjoy the innocence and comedy of the fifties
Ordered Volume 1-5. Got two copies of disc 1 and no disc 2.
FUNNY GOOD CLEAN FUN NOT AVAILABLE ON TV THESE DAYS.
Outstanding!! The great old days,
Love the collection but one disk was damaged (actually it looks like a manufacturing defect).  Unfortunately didn't realize it until after the return window so we're missing a disk.
excellent show after all of these years

Was disappointed with this buy. I wanted series not jumping all around to different episodes. Very missed up.
hugely retro and funny.

The program content is outstanding and very entertaining.  The disc is the problem.  The rendition is not what it should be.  The programs were on black and white film that should be a good source.  There no excuse for issuing programs on a DVD-R.  Disc 1 did not play as is often the case with DVD-Rs.  I ordered another that did play.
Great ! Thanks
The show was good but out of order they jumped all over the place I expected they would start at the beginning of the series and not jump all over the place I will not be getting any more.
My sister gave me this set for Christmas.  I have no problem with the content but the set had 2 vol 4 disks and no vol 2 disk.  Since it was a gift I do not know how to correct the problem.

Orded this for a family member for Christmas. First set arrived with no Volume 2 DVD. Instead, Volume 4 was in the Volume 2 case.
Checked the Volume 4 case, and it also contained Volume 4. Thus, returned the set for a replacement. New set arrives with the Volume 3 case broken. And now no option for a replacement - refund only. You'd like to think that if you order something it would arrive in tact and accurate.
This was a gift that was loved as soon as it was opened. I would still like to get a replacement, but one without damage.

Please note - Volumes 6-11 was also purchase at the same time. 1 case arrived broken. Still awaiting replacement set.

So many of the episodes were so true to life. Why can't they make them like they use to? So much now is just trash.
